 ABUJA – The Executive Director, Rural Electrification Fund, Rural Electrification Agency, Dr. Sanu­si Ohiare, has urged Nigerians to embrace peace, especially in this period of Eid- el Kabir cel­ebration. Felicitating with all Muslim faithfuls in the celebration of this year’s Eid- el Kabir, Sanusi, in his message, urged all Mus­lims in the country and indeed across the globe to imbibe the spirit of the celebration which is centered on sacrifice, love and obedience to the will of Al­mighty Allah. He said the exemplary life of the Holy Prophet Muhammad (May the peace and blessings of Allah be upon him), enjoined Muslim faithfuls to have faith and trust in Almighty Allah, adding that with faith all things are possible in the sight of the Creator. SAMUEL OGIDAN ABUJA – The Executive Director, Rural Electrification Fund, Rural Electrification Agency, Dr. Sanu­si Ohiare, has urged Nigerians to embrace peace, especially in this period of Eid- el Kabir cel­ebration. Felicitating with all Muslim faithfuls in the celebration of this year’s Eid- el Kabir, Sanusi, in his message, urged all Mus­lims in the country and indeed across the globe to imbibe the spirit of the celebration which is centered on sacrifice, love and obedience to the will of Al­mighty Allah. He said the exemplary life of the Holy Prophet Muhammad (May the peace and blessings of Allah be upon him), enjoined Muslim faithfuls to have faith and trust in Almighty Allah, adding that with faith all things are possible in the sight of the Creator.